      "message": "If a fragment shader has, e.g., two unassigned outputs, and an application does not assign bindings through API calls, the spec requires automatic assignment. To avoid relying on loosely-defined driver behavior, ANGLE assigns them internally and calls `glBindFragDataLocationEXT` for each output that has not been assigned in the fragment shader.\n\nSince Adreno drivers do not properly support `glBindFragDataLocationEXT`, such assignments fail. There are only two possible resolutions here:\n\n- Ignore Adreno bugs as they are not reachable from WebGL and ensure that Skia uses shader-assigned outputs.\n\n- Defer shader compilation until program linking when this extension is used on Adreno and rewrite fragment output declarations according to API bindings.",
